!Special Shit
*''Spirit'' (SP): Each round, every living party member contributes a number of SP to a party pool equal to his or her level. SP are used to cast spells and use special abilities, which are character-specific.
*''Luck'': The player gains 7 Luck at the beginning of the game, which are refreshed at the beginning of a new chapter. 1 point allows a character an extra reaction in a turn. One point an be burned (permanently reducing your maximum Luck) to keep a character alive.
!Base Attributes
||Power|Finesse|Resistance|h
|!Physical|Strength|Dexterity|Constitution|
|!Mental|Intelligence|Wisdom|Willpower|
|!Social|Charisma|Fellowship|Composure|
*''Race'': Determines Size and a few other characteristics, like stat bonuses
!Derived Statistics
*''Size'': Determined by Race
*''Hit Points'': 2 × (Constitution + Willpower)
*''Speed'': Strength + Dexterity
*''Initiative'': Dexterity + Intelligence + Composure
*''Defense'': 10 + 3 × (Dexterity + Wisdom) - 2 × Size
*''Resilience'': Size + other modifiers +1 if Dwarf.
*''Level'': Highest value of any Professional Skill
!Skills
*''Acrobatics'': Used for dodging and feats of dexterity.
*''Athletics'': Used for breaking things or using a feat of great strength.
*''Mêlée'': Used for attacking in melee combat and parrying.
*''Missiles'': Used for attacking in ranged combat.
*''Negotiation'': Used for coercing, convincing, and ascertaining others.
*''Notice'': Used for spotting things.
*''Sneak'': Used for hiding and sneaking around.
!Professional Skills
*''Mage'': Used for attacking with magical spells and supernatural effects.
*''Monk'': Grants bonuses to attack and damage with natural weapons and unarmed attacks.
*''Priest'': Used for healing creatures and summoning divine powers.
*''Thief'': Used for picking pockets and disabling traps and/or locks.
*''Warrior'': Grants bonuses to attack and damage with manufactured weapons.
!Races
~~
*''Human'': +1 to the spirit pool every round. +1 Intelligence, Wisdom and Willpower. Size 4.
*''Elf'': +1 Intelligence and Dexterity, +1 Mêlée, Missiles, and Notice. Size 3.
*''Dwarf'': +1 Constitution and Willpower, Use Constitution instead of Dexterity for Defense. +1 Resilience. Size 3.
*''Gnome'': +1 Intelligence and Fellowship, +1 Arcana, Thievery, and Notice. Size 3.
*''Halfling'': +1 Fellowship and Charisma. +1 Thievery. Use Dexterity to determine Defense instead of Wisdom (so 6 × Dexterity). Size 2.
*''Orc'': +1 Strength and Constitution, +1 Mêlée, Warrior, and Athletics. +2 Defense. Size 4.
~~

!Advancement & Experience Points
*You may advance your characters at any time, even in combat.
*Every time you fell an enemy, you gain 1 Experience Point (XP). Particularly difficult enemies may grant 2 XP upon defeat. Bosses give 5 XP.
*Advancing a character costs a number of XP according what you want to advance.
*Experience is not handled per-character; rather, it is a global pool of points that can be spent advancing anyone in your party.

|>| Advancing a character: XP costs |h
| +1 to a base attribute | 2 XP × current rank |
| +1 to a current skill | 1 XP × current rank |
| New skill | 2 XP |
| New profession | 3 XP |
| +1 to a current profession | 2 XP × current rank |
| Gain a perk | 2 XP |
|Note that you may have no more perks than twice your level, plus one. The only way to increase your level is by improving existing professions.|c
*The interesting bit about the level advancement method is that every character has unique perks for each profession. Many perks have prerequisite ranks in professional skills.
