!Characters
*''Hero'' -- a leader and a commander for the forces. Fully customizable by the player, down to name and race. If (s)he dies, though, it's game over.
*''Ballin'' -- Ballin Stonehearth, a sturdy dwarf whose relaxed attitude masks his incredible combat ferocity.
*''Imlir'' -- Imlir Oakenfold, a lithe elf who feels the pressure of his kin to make something of himself.
*''Calem'' -- Calem Taylor, a quiet human with a volley of hidden bravery and strength.
*''Fnipper'' -- "Fnipper", a gnomish inventor, tinker, and alchemist.
*''Alder'' -- Alder Brushgather, a halfling whose short stature (even for a halfling) gets him in and out of interesting places.
*''Korôk'' -- Korôk Gorrá, a very muscular, illiterate orc with poor social skills.
*''Reimann'' -- Reimann ~LaGrange, a human that exudes an aura of supernatural wrongness. He's got the heart of a warrior in the body of a wizard.
*''Tamantha'' -- Tamantha Badgerclaw, a halfling raised in the human lands, and knows a few of their tricks.
*''Dodók'' -- Dodók Sabrefrenzies, a dwarvish librarian and compiler of secret lore. She was the sole survivor of a great tragedy.
*''Gorton'' -- Gorton Axebeard, a dwarf veteran of grand siege. He's aged a bit since the war, but he still fights like no other.
*''Jorina'' -- Jorina Crowsbeak, a human that's also possibly half-giant. She towers over her comrades and can reach farther than they can.
*''Portia'' -- Portia Glittergem, an elf raised by gnomes. She is very skilled with a bow.
*''Broglie'' -- Broglie Alexandrite, a troglodyte tired of a secluded existence, wanting to integrate within normal society. His inherent stench is a bit off-putting.
*''Dervish'' -- Dervish Graymoon, an elf with a deep connection to the woodlands and the feykind. He knows the woodlands like the back of his hand.
*''Kran'' -- Kran Gootcha, a goblin shaman with bizzare powers. Her strange powers aid her in surprising ways.
*''Jacinth'' -- Jacinth Korl, an aging orc with a mysterious connection to the sky. The weather changes at his command.